It seemed obvious that they KNEW they were not supposed to be there, and that they said they had done this before.  I am not pointing this out so that their priveledges could be revoked, or they be punished.  I point it out because what they did seems no more or less serious than what Chopstickz did.  It seems they knew better, but chose to disregard the rules.<br>
<br>
You say they &quot;worked it out.&quot;  Well, it worked out for Jagg(?) also, I read he got to turn in the item.  Does that make it OK?  Apparently so in one case, not in the other.<br>
<br>
I guess it is just me, but I ask myself &quot;Why only the individual being flamed?&quot;  Perhaps it is just my admitted aversion to large guilds (me being in a small guild) revealing itself, but when I read large guilds saying and doing these things with nary a critisism, then individuals being blasted for no more or less, I find it troubling.<br>
