OOOOOooo, I see now. You think that following the rules when it benefits you is *wrong*, even if you also follow rules when they don't benefit you. Ok, I get it. See, we're crossing wires there. I call that behavior &quot;fair&quot;, being that you abide by the consequences of the rules, and also don't expect more benefit than anyone else would get. See, wrong, to me, implies a negative action or thought process. I bet that's the source of all our confusion. <br>
