All of your examples imply a *negative action* on the part of the person being morally wrong. Someone is emotionally abusive. Someone is rude. Someone burns food. Someone does something morally reprehensible. You know what's *not* morally reprehensible? Wanting to do something in the game, even if it runs contrary to what someone else wants. <br>
<br>
This is why they are incorrect examples, and serve only to inflame by giving obviously exaggerated real life examples for an in game situation, about which you had this to say.<br>
