Yama's mistake WAS a mistake, and one that was quickly and not too painfully rectified by them, and I don't think they will be doing the same thing again. If they do, well, as Milambus said, THEN the flames may rise but this situation and it's resolution don't require flaming, everything was handled as well as possible by all involved I think.<br>
<br>
Chops deliberately did an @#%$ thing WITH malice of forethought with a 'scorched earth' mentality (if I can't have it, NO ONE CAN HAVE IT') and hasn't apologized NOR made any attempt to rectify that I can gather from this thread.<br>
